Subtyped pathogen structure

Source: R/pathogen_structure.R
subtyped.Rd

Subtyped pathogen structure

Usage

subtyped(
  data,
  case_timeseries,
  time,
  influenzaA_unsubtyped_timeseries,
  influenzaA_subtyped_timeseries,
  other_pathogen_timeseries
)

Arguments

data

dataframe containing columns with all relevant data

case_timeseries

name of column with total case data, this name will be used as the name of the pathogen

time

name of column with time data. flexible format - can be date, index, or others, accepted as index identifiers in the tsibble time format.

influenzaA_unsubtyped_timeseries

vector of column names with additional unsubtyped influenzaA case count timeseries

influenzaA_subtyped_timeseries

vector of column names with additional subtyped influenzaA case count timeseries

other_pathogen_timeseries

vector of column names with additional pathogen case count timeseries to model

Value

named list including pathogen_structure, pathogen_names, and data of class EpiStrainDynamics.pathogen_structure

See also

Other pathogen_structure: multiple(), single()

Examples

subtyped(
  data = influenza,
  case_timeseries = 'ili',
  time = 'week',
  influenzaA_unsubtyped_timeseries = 'inf_A',
  influenzaA_subtyped_timeseries = c('inf_H3N2', 'inf_H1N1'),
  other_pathogen_timeseries = c('inf_B', 'other')
)
